article.description: Keenan Black threw a touchdown pass to Trey Gross, then threw for the two-point conversion, with nine seconds remaining to give Delaware State a 33-30 edge over Morgan State on Saturday.
article.headline: Delaware State rallies late to beat Morgan State 33-30
article.linkText: Delaware State rallies late to beat Morgan State 33-30
article.story: DOVER, Del. -- Keenan Black threw a touchdown pass to Trey Gross, then threw for the two-point conversion, with nine seconds remaining to give Delaware State a 33-30 edge over Morgan State on Saturday. The Hornets (2-8, 2-6 MEAC) trailed 30-25 when Black fired a 3-yard touchdown to Gross with nine seconds left to play and followed that with a two-point conversion pass for the final score. Delaware fell behind 21-0 early in the second quarter and was down 23-13 at the break. A Wisdom Nzidee field goal midway through the third and a 23-yard scoring pass from Black to Kwannah Kollie tied it up at 23-all as the quarter ended. Black finished with 234 yards and four touchdowns passing. Nyfease West ran for 119 yards on 19 carries. DeAndre Harris threw for 283 yards and three touchdowns for the Bears (1-9, 1-6). --- More AP college football: http://www.collegefootball.ap.org and http://www.twitter.com/AP-Top25
